The effects of K1 and Na1 ions on ADP binding In the cytosol, Hsp70 requires a Kþ ion, rather than a Naþ ion, for its ATP hydrolysis and refolding activities.28,29 The major reason may be that the Kþ ion is larger than the Naþ ion, and thus, appropriately shifts the orientation of the triphosphate group of ATP, to facilitate ATP hydrolysis by Hsp70. However, it has also been reported that the Kd value of bovine Hsc70 for ADP in the presence of Naþ ion is the same as that in the presence of Kþ ion.28 In this context, we examined the effects of Kþ and Naþ ions on the ADP binding.

