The NBD sample was concentrated to about
10 mg/mL. To obtain the crystal of the ADP- and Mg2þ ion-bound NBD containing Kþ ion (Crystal
1), the protein sample was mixed with ADP,
MgCl2, and phosphate-K buffer (pH 8.0) at final concentrations of 5 mM, 5 mM, and 20 mM,
respectively and crystallized by the sitting-drop
vapor-diffusion method at 293 K, against the reser-
voir solution [0.1 M Bis–Tris buffer (pH 5.5), con-
taining 0.05 M CaCl2 and 30 % polyethylene glycol monomethyl ether 500]. The crystal belonged to
the space group P212121, with unit-cell parameters a ¼ 45.73 A˚ , b ¼ 61.34 A˚ , c ¼ 142.65 A˚ , a ¼ b ¼ c ¼ 90.00. To obtain the crystal of the ADP-bound and Mg2þ-free NBD (Crystal 2), the protein sample
was mixed with ADP and EDTA to final concen-
trations of 5 mM, and crystallized by the same
method, against the reservoir solution [0.1 M Bis–
Tris buffer (pH 5.5), containing 0.25 M KNO3 and 25% polyethylene glycol 3350]. The crystal
belonged to the space group P212121, with unit-cell parameters a ¼ 45.86 A˚ , b ¼ 63.14 A˚ , c ¼ 144.22 A˚ , a ¼ b ¼ c ¼ 90.00. To obtain the crystal of the ADP- and Mg2þ ion-bound NBD containing Naþ ion (Crystal 3), the protein sample was mixed
with ADP and MgCl2 to final concentrations of 5 mM and crystallized by the same method, against
the reservoir solution [0.1 M HEPES buffer (pH
7.0), containing 0.15 M MgCl2 and 30% polyethylene glycol monomethyl ether 500]. The crystal
belonged to the space group P212121, with unit-cell parameters a ¼ 46.11 A˚ , b ¼ 63.68 A˚ , c ¼ 143.53 A˚ , a ¼ b ¼ c ¼ 90.00.

Data collection and structure determination Crystal 1 was directly flash cooled in liquid nitrogen. The diffraction data were measured at the BL-17A beamline of the Photon Factory (Tsukuba, Japan) at

a wavelength of 1.54 A˚ . Crystal 2 was cryoprotected with 15% glycerol in the reservoir solution and was flash cooled in liquid nitrogen. The diffraction data were collected at the BL26B2 beamline of SPring-8 (Harima, Japan) at wavelengths of 1.00 and 1.54 A˚ . Crystal 3 was cryoprotected with 15% glycerol in the reservoir solution and was flash cooled in liquid nitrogen. The diffraction data were collected at the BL26B2 beamline of SPring-8 at a wavelength of 1.00 A˚ . All X-ray diffraction data were processed using the HKL2000 program.35 The initial phases were determined by the molecular replacement method with the program MOLREP,27 using the structure of the human Hsp70 NBD in the AMPPNP-bound state (PDB ID: 2E8A)34 as the search model. Next, we used the CNS programs36 and the Refmac5 program37 to refine the structures, and modified the protein models with the TURBOFRODO program (http://www.afmb.univ-mrs.fr/TURBO-) and the Coot program.38 The ADP, Pi, and PEG molecules and the Mg2þ, Naþ, Kþ, ClÀ, and Ca2þ ions were added into the electron densities, which were visible in the Fo À Fc map. All of the numbers and distances of the coordinate bonds between the metal ions and the oxygen atoms are appropriate,39 and the anomalous signals of the Kþ, ClÀ, and Ca2þ ions were observed in the anomalous difference Fourier maps. Anomalous difference peaks in Crystals 1 and 2 are listed in Table III. Crystal 3 contained Pi, which was probably derived from the small amount of Pi in the ADP sample, as Pi was not added to the NBD sample for purification and crystallization. The final refined model of the ADPand Mg2þ ion-bound NBD containing Kþ ion achieved an R/Rfree of 18.9/21.3, that of the ADPbound and Mg2þ ion-free NBD achieved an R/Rfree of 18.6/20.8, and that of the ADP- and Mg2þ ion-bound NBD containing Naþ ion achieved an R/Rfree of 18.6/ 21.8. The final models had no Ramachandran violations, as confirmed by PROCHECK.40 The atomic coordinates and structure factors have been deposited in the Protein Data Bank (accession codes: 3AY9 for the structure of the ADP- and Mg2þ ionbound NBD containing Kþ ion, 3ATV for the structure of the ADP-bound and Mg2þ-free NBD, and 3ATU for the structure of the ADP- and Mg2þ ionbound NBD containing Naþ ion).
